{
  "$description": "Light-world hue steps (Paper + Linen contexts). Ratified 2026-07-13 after the four-theme eyeball pass: tints strengthened from the first draft (C 0.04→0.058, L 0.955→0.945), lines strengthened (L 0.72→0.65). tint-ink is same-hue dark ink — the monochromatic chip idiom: on light ground the ink carries the hue identity (§4), verified ≥ Lc 60 on its tint. Values are per-hue literals so any hue can be re-tuned independently; the shared L/C is a starting symmetry, not a formula contract. ring added 2026-07-17 (Phase C adjudication): the world-varying focus-ring/accent-signal step — world-independent solids cannot clear ring contrast on both polarities; in the light world the ring IS the solid (alias).",

  "world": {
    "register-step": { "$type": "number", "$value": 0.018, "$extensions": { "alx": { "role": "the light-world register quantum (ratified 2026-07-13): one perceptual step of ΔL. State deltas are authored and adjusted in multiples of this — 'one step quieter' is arithmetic, not taste archaeology. OKLCH L is perceptually uniform, so a fixed step feels the same anywhere on the ramp; dark worlds need a larger step (polarity)." } } }
  },

